<file path="README.md">
AURAX | Architectural Footwear & Kinetic Engineering

AURAX is a premium, minimalist e-commerce experience designed for high-end architectural footwear. The project blends cinematic editorial presentation with precise engineering, offering a "Laboratory" aesthetic that mirrors the technical innovation of the products themselves.

🧪 The Concept
AURAX was born in a modular studio in Stockholm with a singular vision: to destroy the boundary between athletic performance and high-fashion aesthetics. Every silhouette is designed as an interface for human movement, treating shoe design with the same rigor as tectonic architecture.

Key Innovations:
- EVO-SOLE: Proprietary carbon-infused polymer providing 42% more energy return.
- AURAX-KNIT: Sustainably sourced technical fibers that adapt to the foot’s unique topography.
- T-STABILITY: Architectural heel counters for stability during high-impact motion.

🚀 Live Demo
Experience the editorial interface and kinetic showcase here: 
https://aurax-luxury-footwear-landing-page.vercel.app/

🛠️ Technical Stack
- Frontend: React 19 (TypeScript)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS 4.0
- Animations: Framer Motion (via motion/react)
- Build Tool: Vite
- Icons: Lucide React
- AI Integration: Google Gemini API (for intelligent features)

💻 Local Setup
Follow these steps to run the AURAX environment locally:

Prerequisites:
- Node.js (LTS version recommended)

Installation:
1. Clone the repository and enter the directory.
2. Install dependencies:
   npm install
3. Environment Configuration:
   - Create a .env.local file in the root directory.
   - Add your Gemini API key:
     GEMINI_API_KEY="YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY_HERE"
4. Launch the development server:
   npm run dev
5. The application will be available at http://localhost:3000.

📂 Project Structure
- /src/components/innovation: Technical showcases and the "Lab" experience.
- /src/components/product: High-end product galleries and selection interfaces.
- /src/context: Global cart and state management.
- /src/pages: Editorial-style pages including "Story" and "Innovation".

🏛️ Project Metadata
- Project Name: AURAX | Luxury Footwear
- Design Language: Cinematic, Minimalist, Editorial
- Core Capabilities: Motion engineering, dynamic cart systems, and responsive architectural layouts.
</file>

